  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): 0.3.7+commit.6020b8bb\r\n* OS: OSX\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): 3.8.0\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nAccording to the [documentation](https://vyper.readthedocs.io/en/stable/scoping-and-declarations.html?highlight=shadow#name-shadowing), it is not permitted for a calldata variable to shadow the name of a storage variable.\r\nHowever this behavior is not enforced as the example provided in the documentation which is not supposed to compile actually compiles:\r\n\r\n`vyper -f  abi,bytecode tests/customs/foo.vy` \r\n```Vyper\r\na: int128\r\n\r\n@external\r\ndef foo(a: int128) -> int128:\r\n    # input argument cannot have the same name as a storage variable\r\n    return a\r\n```\r\n```\r\n[{\"stateMutability\": \"nonpayable\", \"type\": \"function\", \"name\": \"foo\", \"inputs\": [{\"name\": \"a\", \"type\": \"int128\"}], \"outputs\": [{\"name\": \"\", \"type\": \"int128\"}]}]\r\n0x61005a61000f60003961005a6000f36003361161000c57610042565b60003560e01c346100485763d98ffe11811861004057602436106100485760043580600f0b81186100485760405260206040f35b505b60006000fd5b600080fda165767970657283000307000b\r\n```\r\nThis issue could maybe be merged with #3132, if it seems relevant I will merge them.\r\n",
